						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the Narasimhasvāmin shrine in the Kallēśvara temple. </p>						

						<p>This is dated in the cyclic year Nandana, Māgha, śu. 10, Sunday. The record is in characters of about the 11th century.</p>						

						<p>It registers a gift of land to Purāṇada Vishṇubhaṭṭa by the fifty <hi rend="italic">mahājanas</hi> of Bāguḷi which bears the appellation <hi rend="italic">Hariśchandradatti.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
